=== TEST 3: write to ngx.header.HEADER (multi-value)
--- http_config eval: $::HttpConfig
--- config
    location = /t {
        set $foo hello;
        content_by_lua '
            for i = 1, 200 do
                ngx.header["Foo"] = {i, i + 1}
            end
            local v = ngx.header["Foo"]
            if type(v) == "table" then
                ngx.say("Foo: ", table.concat(v, ", "))
            else
                ngx.say("Foo: ", v)
            end
        ';
    }
--- request
GET /t
--- response_body
Foo: 200, 201

--- error_log eval
qr/\[TRACE   \d+ "content_by_lua":2 loop\]/
--- no_error_log
[error]
